So you want to change the font on your website and you want it to be a funkier font? Google appears to lower their competitors in Google search results so I figured I would give them a fighting chance.

PrimaryBlogger[1] has the Google Font API plugin enabled by default. Â You can install the plugin from the "Add New" tab under the plugins section of your WordPress admin. Or, upload the plugin folder to your server and do it the old fashioned way.

